HEADWORD: Biacid
<hw>Bi*ac"id</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>acid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Having
two hydrogen atoms which can be replaced by negative atoms or radicals
to form salts; -- said of bases. See <er>Diacid</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

